{{wikipedia}}
===Noun Phrase===
'''whole number'''

# An [[integer]] greater than zero; a member of the infinite sequence {1, 2, 3, ...}.
#: ''The calculated answer was 4.32, but we'll round to the nearest '''whole number''', 4.''
# A [[non-negative]] [[integer]]; a member of the infinite sequence {0, 1, 2, 3, ...}.
#: ''Since the amount was less than half, and a '''whole number''' was required, the result was 0.''

===Usage Note===
Note that the whole numbers are sometimes taken to include zero, similar to the [[natural numbers]].   Rarely they are taken to be the [[integers]]. They are ''countable'' or ''denumerable'', the set having size [[aleph-null]].

